The article highlights the importance of National Teen Dating Violence Awareness and Prevention Month, emphasizing the need to end the cycle of teen dating violence that affects many young people. The author mentions that dating violence can take various forms, including physical, sexual, emotional abuse, bullying, and shaming, both in person and through electronic communication and social media. The consequences of violent dating relationships can lead to depression, anxiety, substance abuse, and even suicidal thoughts. The article encourages Americans to promote healthy relationships, protect teens from abuse, and ensure they have access to support. It also provides resources for immediate and confidential assistance for those involved in abusive relationships. The proclamation by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. designates February 2021 as National Teen Dating Violence Awareness and Prevention Month and calls upon all Americans to support efforts to empower young people and prevent and respond to teen dating violence.